    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/welsh-rarebit-beef-burger-with-mustard-mayo-and-pickles/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chips are cooking, slice your <strong>cucumber</strong> finely</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced cucumber</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>cider vinegar</strong>,<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and set aside to pickle \u2013 these are your <strong>pickles</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/welsh-rarebit-beef-burger-with-mustard-mayo-and-pickles/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>mince</strong> in a bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until thoroughly combined (clean hands are the best way!), then shape into 1 patty per person</p><p>Meanwhile, melt a knob of <strong>butter</strong> in a pot over a medium heat</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/welsh-rarebit-beef-burger-with-mustard-mayo-and-pickles/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once melted, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms</p><p>Gradually whisk in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>milk</strong>, a little at a time, and cook for 2-3 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Once thickened, add the <strong>grated cheese</strong> with <strong>half </strong>your <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> and a pinch of<strong> pepper </strong>and cook for a further 2 min or until the cheese has melted, then remove the pan from the heat \u2013 this is your <strong>rarebit sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/welsh-rarebit-beef-burger-with-mustard-mayo-and-pickles/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>patty[ies]</strong>, press down firmly with a spatula and cook for 5 min</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 5? You may need to do this in batches!</p><p>Flip the <strong>patty[ies]</strong> and reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 5 min further until cooked through and charred (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/welsh-rarebit-beef-burger-with-mustard-mayo-and-pickles/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, transfer the <strong>burger[s]</strong> to a separate <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) and top with the <strong>rarebit sauce</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 5-6 min or until the rarebit sauce is lightly browned \u2013 this is your <strong>Welsh rarebit burger</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/welsh-rarebit-beef-burger-with-mustard-mayo-and-pickles/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the burger is cooking, slice your <strong>ciabatta[s] </strong>in half and place in the <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until warmed through and golden</p><p>Combine the <strong>remaining wholegrain mustard</strong> (not a fan of mustard? Just add a little!) and your <strong>mayo </strong>in a bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>wholegrain mustard mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/welsh-rarebit-beef-burger-with-mustard-mayo-and-pickles/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To build your burger, spread the <strong>wholegrain mustard mayo</strong> over a <strong>ciabatta base</strong>, then top with some of the <strong>pickles</strong>, a <strong>Welsh rarebit burger </strong>and a <strong>ciabatta lid</strong></p><p>Serve with the <strong>chips </strong>and <strong>remaining pickles </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
